// Detection 1: Account Takeover via MFA Fatigue
//
// What it finds:
//   High-risk sign-ins, which surfaces the full dmorris attack chain in order:
//   password guessing from a foreign IP, an MFA challenge, repeated denied MFA
//   pushes (the fatigue attack), and the final successful sign-in once the user
//   caved. All from the same malicious IP (102.89.34.180, Lagos NG).
//
// Why it works:
//   Microsoft Entra ID Protection scores risky sign-ins. Filtering to
//   RiskLevelDuringSignIn == "high" strips ~50 benign records down to just the
//   attack, and sorting by time reconstructs the kill chain.
//
// MITRE ATT&CK:
//   T1110 Brute Force, T1621 MFA Request Generation (MFA fatigue),
//   T1078 Valid Accounts

SigninLogs_CL
| where RiskLevelDuringSignIn == "high"
| project TimeGenerated, UserPrincipalName, IPAddress, Location, ResultDescription, MfaResult, ConditionalAccessStatus
| sort by TimeGenerated asc
